1
00:02:23,439 --> 00:02:23,919
Hello?

2
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:25,800
[Qing Ye, it's me.]

3
00:02:26,639 --> 00:02:28,280
[Mom said you had dinner with her.]

4
00:02:28,599 --> 00:02:29,400
[You're back in Beijing?]

5
00:02:30,599 --> 00:02:31,199
Yeah, back.

6
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:33,199
[Congrats.]

7
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:34,400
[You're back to normal life.]

8
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:37,000
Thanks.

9
00:02:38,439 --> 00:02:40,120
[You don't sound too happy.]

10
00:02:40,840 --> 00:02:41,360
Do I?

11
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:43,039
Maybe,

12
00:02:43,719 --> 00:02:45,199
I'm still getting used to it.

13
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:47,199
[No way.]

14
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:48,639
Yeah.

15
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:50,800
Zhazhating has fewer skyscrapers,

16
00:02:52,199 --> 00:02:53,639
the lights aren't as bright,

17
00:02:54,759 --> 00:02:56,280
and the air always carries

18
00:02:56,280 --> 00:02:57,120
a hint of the sea.

19
00:02:58,360 --> 00:02:59,400
By all rights,

20
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:03,000
I should be happy to be back.

21
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:05,919
But…

22
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,319
[But you miss that place.]

23
00:03:15,080 --> 00:03:15,800
You're right.

24
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:40,159
Wu,

25
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:41,400
dinner's ready.

26
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:42,360
Come eat.

27
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:17,959
[Hurry up, we're late.]

28
00:04:18,199 --> 00:04:19,439
[Coming!]

29
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:24,759
[I haven't done my hair!]

30
00:04:25,199 --> 00:04:26,519
[Three minutes till late.]

31
00:04:26,839 --> 00:04:27,920
[Late means time-out.]

32
00:04:29,439 --> 00:04:30,000
[Alright.]
[Move.]

33
00:05:00,199 --> 00:05:01,920
I've been running around lately,

34
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:04,279
didn't really get to

35
00:05:04,759 --> 00:05:05,959
look after Ye.

36
00:05:06,399 --> 00:05:07,759
She didn't even get

37
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:10,439
her favorite red bean zongzi.

38
00:05:11,279 --> 00:05:12,199
I thought

39
00:05:12,199 --> 00:05:13,920
she'd stay through Lantern Festival.

40
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:16,959
Didn't expect her to leave in such a rush.

41
00:05:23,319 --> 00:05:24,759
What are you all

42
00:05:24,759 --> 00:05:25,639
so down about?

43
00:05:26,079 --> 00:05:26,759
Ye

44
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:28,240
just left

45
00:05:28,240 --> 00:05:29,720
our little dump,

46
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:31,759
she's back

47
00:05:31,759 --> 00:05:32,959
in her rich nest.

48
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:33,959
That's a good thing.

49
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:35,279
What's there to mope about?

50
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:39,639
Good thing.

51
00:05:40,560 --> 00:05:41,079
Yeah.

52
00:05:42,519 --> 00:05:43,279
I just feel

53
00:05:43,279 --> 00:05:44,680
the house is missing someone.

54
00:05:45,279 --> 00:05:47,040
Feels empty now.

55
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:48,959
People come

56
00:05:49,360 --> 00:05:50,439
and people go.

57
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:52,600
Just like the seasons.

58
00:05:53,439 --> 00:05:54,879
Spring sunshine and blossoms,

59
00:05:55,120 --> 00:05:55,720
so wonderful.

60
00:05:56,319 --> 00:05:57,639
But it doesn't last.

61
00:05:58,279 --> 00:06:00,040
We also have hot summers and cold winters.

62
00:06:00,519 --> 00:06:02,519
Can't live missing spring forever

63
00:06:02,519 --> 00:06:03,839
and forget the rest.

64
00:06:05,519 --> 00:06:06,199
So,

65
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:08,040
just live your life well now,

66
00:06:08,319 --> 00:06:09,800
spring will come again.

67
00:06:10,439 --> 00:06:11,120
The ones who leave,

68
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:12,519
you'll see them again.

69
00:06:14,079 --> 00:06:14,519
Eat up.

70
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:30,560
Finally home.

71
00:06:31,519 --> 00:06:32,560
Everything's cleaned up.

72
00:06:32,879 --> 00:06:34,199
The old nanny's back too.

73
00:06:34,399 --> 00:06:35,959
Need anything, just ask her.

74
00:06:36,079 --> 00:06:37,120
Okay, thanks, Mr. Sun.

75
00:06:38,759 --> 00:06:39,639
Ye, you're back.
Welcome home!

76
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:41,560
Come in!

77
00:06:41,839 --> 00:06:42,920
Long time no see, ma'am.

78
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:43,439
Come in.

79
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:47,079
Alright.

80
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:48,360
Enough.

81
00:06:49,319 --> 00:06:49,959
Careful, it's hot.

82
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:51,319
Call me when you're done.
Okay.

83
00:07:20,959 --> 00:07:21,800
[Is this still alive?]
[Come take a look.]

84
00:07:23,839 --> 00:07:24,519
[It is!]

85
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:25,720
[The welwitschia made it!]

86
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:29,519
Mom.

87
00:07:30,160 --> 00:07:30,879
Take this.

88
00:07:31,439 --> 00:07:32,160
What's this?

89
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:34,160
My pay from lately.

90
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:35,040
Not much.

91
00:07:35,319 --> 00:07:36,439
Give it to Auntie Shanxi

92
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:37,560
for rent.

93
00:07:38,079 --> 00:07:38,839
I've got money.

94
00:07:39,120 --> 00:07:40,120
Keep it.

95
00:07:40,519 --> 00:07:41,839
School's starting soon.

96
00:07:41,839 --> 00:07:43,120
Then college after that.

97
00:07:43,879 --> 00:07:44,639
Save the money up.

98
00:07:44,959 --> 00:07:45,800
Where'd you get money?

99
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:47,920
When Qing Ye's dad left,

100
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:49,120
he lent me some money.

101
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:50,279
A hundred grand.
A hundred…

102
00:07:51,399 --> 00:07:52,680
I know what you're thinking.

103
00:07:52,920 --> 00:07:54,240
But it's not like that.

104
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:55,279
Don't worry.

105
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:56,639
I didn't squeeze him for it.

106
00:07:56,959 --> 00:07:57,720
And I'm not
some money-grubber either.

107
00:07:59,959 --> 00:08:00,560
This money,

108
00:08:00,879 --> 00:08:02,079
he offered it himself.

109
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:03,519
He didn't ask for it back,
but I wouldn't agree.

110
00:08:04,959 --> 00:08:06,360
It's all in writing,

111
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:07,680
clear as day.

112
00:08:07,879 --> 00:08:09,519
No matter how long it takes,
I'll pay it back

113
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:10,720
Don't worry.

114
00:08:12,519 --> 00:08:13,079
So…

115
00:08:13,759 --> 00:08:14,720
Does Qing Ye know?

116
00:08:17,839 --> 00:08:18,800
I think so.

117
00:08:19,560 --> 00:08:20,680
Probably she was the one

118
00:08:21,079 --> 00:08:23,079
who asked her dad to give the money.

119
00:08:26,519 --> 00:08:27,680
Look at them,

120
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:29,759
a hundred grand,

121
00:08:29,759 --> 00:08:31,240
and no sweat to them.

122
00:08:32,559 --> 00:08:34,039
If it were us two,

123
00:08:34,639 --> 00:08:36,120
who knows how long we'd have to save?

124
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:38,320
Worlds apart.

125
00:08:41,519 --> 00:08:42,519
Keep it safe.

126
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:44,159
Money doesn't come easy.

127
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:54,360
Ye,

128
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:56,279
your dad headed back to work.

129
00:08:57,120 --> 00:08:58,720
Tons waiting on him.

130
00:08:59,399 --> 00:09:00,080
School starts tomorrow,

131
00:09:00,240 --> 00:09:01,840
I'll take you in the morning.

132
00:09:02,279 --> 00:09:03,000
Get some rest.
- I'm off.
- Okay.

133
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:04,799
Bye, Mr. Sun.

134
00:09:31,919 --> 00:09:32,559
Mom,

135
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:35,120
I'm home.

136
00:11:56,240 --> 00:11:56,919
Gaokao's only

137
00:11:57,159 --> 00:11:58,440
one semester away.

138
00:11:58,720 --> 00:12:00,399
We're heading

139
00:12:00,399 --> 00:12:01,720
into the final sprint.

140
00:12:02,519 --> 00:12:03,440
I hope everyone

141
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:04,759
gives it everything

142
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:05,679
and fights

143
00:12:06,279 --> 00:12:07,600
for the best future you can get.

144
00:12:09,919 --> 00:12:10,360
Class starts.

145
00:12:46,519 --> 00:12:47,919
Mom, how's the color?

146
00:12:48,360 --> 00:12:48,840
Sir,

147
00:12:49,440 --> 00:12:49,879
thanks for the hard work,
have some water.

148
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:51,440
Here.

149
00:12:52,559 --> 00:12:53,039
Sir,

150
00:12:53,519 --> 00:12:54,919
have some water.

151
00:12:57,759 --> 00:12:58,200
Grandma.

152
00:12:58,720 --> 00:12:59,279
Sir,

153
00:12:59,600 --> 00:13:00,519
have some water.

154
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:01,799
Thanks.

155
00:13:03,679 --> 00:13:04,240
Sir,

156
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:05,559
here, grab a bottle.

157
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:06,639
Thanks.

158
00:13:07,159 --> 00:13:07,639
Have some water.
Thanks.

159
00:13:30,399 --> 00:13:31,559
[It's alive, it's Welwitschia.]

160
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:33,600
[Tough as nails.]

161
00:13:33,919 --> 00:13:34,799
[It can survive in the desert]

162
00:13:34,799 --> 00:13:35,840
[for ages and ages.]

163
00:15:04,120 --> 00:15:04,639
Class,

164
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:05,679
I've handed out

165
00:15:05,679 --> 00:15:06,799
my 20 key

166
00:15:06,799 --> 00:15:07,840
scoring tricks.

167
00:15:07,919 --> 00:15:09,399
Memorize the steps.

168
00:15:09,639 --> 00:15:10,159
From now on,

169
00:15:10,559 --> 00:15:11,840
if you get a similar question

170
00:15:11,840 --> 00:15:12,399
and don't know how to solve it,

171
00:15:12,559 --> 00:15:13,799
just plug in the steps.

172
00:15:14,159 --> 00:15:14,679
Remember,

173
00:15:15,240 --> 00:15:15,759
Math

174
00:15:15,799 --> 00:15:17,279
can be memorized by rote learning too.

175
00:15:17,799 --> 00:15:19,720
If you're unsure in the exam,

176
00:15:20,080 --> 00:15:21,000
don't leave it blank,

177
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:22,519
write whatever you can!

178
00:15:22,759 --> 00:15:23,519
For English,

179
00:15:23,600 --> 00:15:25,679
review vocab and grammar.

180
00:15:26,279 --> 00:15:27,519
Cram as much as you can.

181
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:29,799
Don't leave either essay blank.

182
00:15:30,120 --> 00:15:31,120
Memorize some stock phrases

183
00:15:31,240 --> 00:15:32,759
and hit the word count.

184
00:15:33,279 --> 00:15:34,320
Get studying.

185
00:15:34,519 --> 00:15:36,679
Last-minute cramming still helps.

186
00:15:36,879 --> 00:15:38,480
Every point counts!

187
00:15:43,159 --> 00:15:43,919
The last holiday

188
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:45,440
before the final showdown.

189
00:15:46,039 --> 00:15:46,759
You've got three days.

190
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:48,519
I hope everyone

191
00:15:49,200 --> 00:15:50,320
gets good rest

192
00:15:50,960 --> 00:15:51,879
and resets their mindset.

193
00:15:52,639 --> 00:15:53,320
But,

194
00:15:53,799 --> 00:15:55,320
don't relax too much.

195
00:15:55,639 --> 00:15:57,919
We've worked hard for three years,

196
00:15:58,519 --> 00:15:59,559
I hope everyone

197
00:16:00,039 --> 00:16:01,320
leaves no regrets.

198
00:16:02,519 --> 00:16:03,759
Go all in for the exams.

199
00:16:04,039 --> 00:16:05,720
Go to the city you want

200
00:16:06,200 --> 00:16:08,120
and get into the university you want.

201
00:16:08,799 --> 00:16:09,360
Keep it up.

202
00:16:10,279 --> 00:16:15,279
- Keep it up!
- Keep it up!

203
00:16:18,279 --> 00:16:19,159
Where do you want to go?

204
00:16:19,840 --> 00:16:22,799
I just want the provincial
normal university,

205
00:16:23,679 --> 00:16:24,399
close to home.

206
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:31,000
Wu, what about you?

207
00:16:47,960 --> 00:16:48,519
Beijing.

208
00:17:10,640 --> 00:17:11,279
Son,

209
00:17:13,240 --> 00:17:14,440
tell your grandma dinner's ready.

210
00:17:15,119 --> 00:17:16,319
One more dish and it's done.

211
00:17:19,079 --> 00:17:20,240
My boy's great.

212
00:17:21,599 --> 00:17:23,200
I love the way you're now!

213
00:17:23,319 --> 00:17:24,640
So focused.

214
00:17:26,240 --> 00:17:27,680
Look at you now,

215
00:17:28,039 --> 00:17:29,759
like those ancient scholars

216
00:17:29,960 --> 00:17:31,680
studying for official exams.

217
00:17:32,279 --> 00:17:32,960
Like

218
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:35,440
"Burning the midnight oil to the extreme."

219
00:17:35,720 --> 00:17:36,640
Is that how it goes?

220
00:17:37,720 --> 00:17:39,039
Yes.

221
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:40,599
Alright.
Then study hard

222
00:17:41,519 --> 00:17:42,359
and call your grandma for dinner later.

223
00:17:42,599 --> 00:17:43,160
Take a break.

224
00:17:43,720 --> 00:17:44,160
Okay.

225
00:17:52,559 --> 00:17:53,119
Grandma.

226
00:18:00,440 --> 00:18:01,039
Grandma.

227
00:18:05,519 --> 00:18:06,039
Grandma.

228
00:18:06,880 --> 00:18:07,359
Grandma?

229
00:18:09,240 --> 00:18:09,880
Dinner's ready.

230
00:18:13,319 --> 00:18:14,000
Wu,

231
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:16,960
I don't wanna eat.

232
00:18:17,279 --> 00:18:18,000
No.

233
00:18:18,599 --> 00:18:19,680
You haven't eaten all day.

234
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:20,519
Come,

235
00:18:21,359 --> 00:18:22,039
I'll carry you downstairs.

236
00:18:29,440 --> 00:18:29,920
Come.

237
00:18:31,839 --> 00:18:32,319
Alright.

238
00:18:35,880 --> 00:18:37,200
Thanks, sweetheart.

239
00:18:38,160 --> 00:18:39,759
I'm no lightweight.

240
00:18:39,880 --> 00:18:40,839
You're lighter than a kitten.

241
00:18:41,319 --> 00:18:42,000
Time to eat!

242
00:18:46,799 --> 00:18:47,880
Grandma, have some soup.

243
00:18:50,119 --> 00:18:50,559
Mom,

244
00:18:51,039 --> 00:18:51,920
with how hard

245
00:18:51,920 --> 00:18:53,519
Wu's studying now,

246
00:18:54,119 --> 00:18:55,240
a top university

247
00:18:55,240 --> 00:18:56,160
is a sure thing.

248
00:18:56,519 --> 00:18:57,319
I'm telling you,

249
00:18:57,519 --> 00:18:58,400
our ancestors

250
00:18:58,400 --> 00:18:59,640
would be smiling down on us.

251
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:04,559
Then the biggest credit goes to Ye.

252
00:19:04,920 --> 00:19:06,960
She got Wu back to school.

253
00:19:07,319 --> 00:19:07,720
Yes,

254
00:19:08,240 --> 00:19:09,160
Grandma is right.

255
00:19:09,680 --> 00:19:10,519
But we still need
to stay calm.

256
00:19:11,680 --> 00:19:13,400
For the gaokao I can only do my best.

257
00:19:14,039 --> 00:19:15,519
Don't think about top universities.

258
00:19:16,240 --> 00:19:17,440
I don't agree.

259
00:19:17,599 --> 00:19:18,799
Why can't we aim high?

260
00:19:19,319 --> 00:19:19,799
Well,

261
00:19:20,039 --> 00:19:21,279
you have to dare to dream.

262
00:19:21,400 --> 00:19:23,359
Hope gives you motivation.

263
00:19:24,799 --> 00:19:26,000
Your mom's right.

264
00:19:27,519 --> 00:19:29,640
I really believe in my grandson.

265
00:19:31,279 --> 00:19:31,759
Come,

266
00:19:32,240 --> 00:19:33,359
have an egg

267
00:19:33,519 --> 00:19:34,359
and get full marks.

268
00:19:35,359 --> 00:19:36,039
Thanks, Grandma.

269
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:42,240
Grandma, let me.

270
00:19:43,720 --> 00:19:44,359
Full marks.

271
00:19:45,319 --> 00:19:45,680
Mom,

272
00:19:45,880 --> 00:19:47,119
you should have an egg too.

273
00:19:47,319 --> 00:19:48,359
Stay 100% healthy!

274
00:19:48,680 --> 00:19:49,519
Okay.

275
00:19:52,359 --> 00:19:53,640
Here's some more good news.

276
00:19:54,240 --> 00:19:55,200
Our Xuan Island salon

277
00:19:55,640 --> 00:19:58,240
is almost finished being renovated.

278
00:19:59,319 --> 00:20:00,680
Once Wu's exams

279
00:20:00,960 --> 00:20:01,920
are over,

280
00:20:02,039 --> 00:20:03,400
I'll get the house sorted

281
00:20:03,720 --> 00:20:04,960
so we can move back home.

282
00:20:05,559 --> 00:20:06,079
Good.

283
00:20:06,680 --> 00:20:07,799
I'm also thinking of

284
00:20:07,880 --> 00:20:09,720
going to a better barbershop

285
00:20:09,720 --> 00:20:10,759
in the city

286
00:20:10,759 --> 00:20:11,799
to learn

287
00:20:11,880 --> 00:20:13,200
and sharpen

288
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:14,319
my skills.

289
00:20:15,319 --> 00:20:16,279
In the future,

290
00:20:16,359 --> 00:20:18,200
things will turn around.

291
00:20:20,200 --> 00:20:20,599
Grandma,

292
00:20:20,759 --> 00:20:22,000
It'll only get better.

293
00:20:23,559 --> 00:20:24,279
That's great.

294
00:20:25,799 --> 00:20:27,759
Tomorrow's the 15th.

295
00:20:28,799 --> 00:20:29,759
Let's go

296
00:20:29,759 --> 00:20:32,200
thank the Dragon King and Mazu

297
00:20:32,920 --> 00:20:33,599
and honor our promises.

298
00:20:34,799 --> 00:20:36,960
I wanna see the sunset too.

299
00:20:38,519 --> 00:20:39,000
Sure.

300
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:40,319
I haven't been out in a while.

301
00:20:41,079 --> 00:20:41,839
I'll go with you.

302
00:20:42,680 --> 00:20:44,440
Forecast says heavy rain tomorrow.

303
00:20:44,880 --> 00:20:45,599
How about

304
00:20:46,119 --> 00:20:47,039
we go together the day after tomorrow,
once the weather clears up.

305
00:20:48,240 --> 00:20:48,920
- Sure.
- Let's go together.
Good.

306
00:20:50,559 --> 00:20:51,319
It's settled then.
Okay.

307
00:20:52,799 --> 00:20:53,240
Alright.

308
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:55,440
The day after.

309
00:20:56,640 --> 00:20:57,960
That works too.

310
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:01,400
Works too…

311
00:21:12,599 --> 00:21:13,240
Wu.

312
00:21:14,640 --> 00:21:15,279
Wu.

313
00:21:16,759 --> 00:21:17,640
Xing Wu!

314
00:21:21,599 --> 00:21:22,319
Xing Wu!

315
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:23,759
Coming!

316
00:21:26,920 --> 00:21:27,519
Wu.
What is it?

317
00:21:28,240 --> 00:21:29,759
Grandma won't wake up
no matter how I call.

318
00:21:29,759 --> 00:21:30,240
What do we do?
Grandma.

319
00:21:31,319 --> 00:21:31,799
Grandma.
Grandma.

320
00:21:38,279 --> 00:21:38,839
Take her to the hospital.
Okay.

321
00:21:40,880 --> 00:21:42,079
Come on.

322
00:21:42,960 --> 00:21:43,640
Slow down.

323
00:22:47,400 --> 00:22:47,880
Doctor.

324
00:22:48,079 --> 00:22:49,039
How's my mom?

325
00:22:50,200 --> 00:22:51,279
The patient's elderly.

326
00:22:52,119 --> 00:22:53,400
Based on post-op indicators

327
00:22:53,599 --> 00:22:54,680
and her condition,

328
00:22:55,279 --> 00:22:56,160
her bodily functions
are very weak.

329
00:22:58,039 --> 00:22:58,799
She can't tolerate

330
00:22:58,799 --> 00:22:59,920
aggressive treatment.

331
00:23:01,079 --> 00:23:03,079
We recommend hospice care.

332
00:23:03,799 --> 00:23:04,640
Prepare for the end.

333
00:23:34,680 --> 00:23:35,200
Mom.

334
00:23:35,680 --> 00:23:36,240
Grandma.

335
00:23:49,279 --> 00:23:49,759
I…

336
00:23:50,640 --> 00:23:51,920
I can't make it.

337
00:23:54,960 --> 00:23:55,400
I…

338
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:56,640
Mom, don't take that off.

339
00:23:57,920 --> 00:23:58,920
It hurts so much.

340
00:23:59,559 --> 00:24:00,079
I…
I…

341
00:24:01,880 --> 00:24:02,440
I…

342
00:24:02,519 --> 00:24:04,440
No intubation.

343
00:24:06,240 --> 00:24:08,200
No resuscitation.

344
00:24:14,799 --> 00:24:15,519
Lanfang.

345
00:24:18,359 --> 00:24:19,599
Guodong…

346
00:24:24,359 --> 00:24:25,920
Mom, you wanna see Xing Guodong?

347
00:24:31,519 --> 00:24:32,519
I know,

348
00:24:34,640 --> 00:24:36,519
he's gone.

349
00:24:45,279 --> 00:24:46,720
How did you know?

350
00:24:49,640 --> 00:24:50,759
Once

351
00:24:52,240 --> 00:24:56,519
you came back very late.

352
00:24:59,359 --> 00:25:03,880
And you were in a bad mood.

353
00:25:06,240 --> 00:25:07,720
I knew

354
00:25:09,279 --> 00:25:11,400
he was gone.

355
00:25:14,200 --> 00:25:15,839
[Leaving so soon?]

356
00:25:15,920 --> 00:25:16,839
[Yes, Mom.]

357
00:25:17,119 --> 00:25:18,279
[I'm going back to town for something.]

358
00:25:18,359 --> 00:25:19,400
[I'll be back in a couple of days.]

359
00:25:20,200 --> 00:25:20,599
[Alright.]

360
00:25:20,839 --> 00:25:22,279
[Take good care of yourself at home.]

361
00:25:22,279 --> 00:25:22,680
[Okay.]
[Be safe.]

362
00:25:23,680 --> 00:25:24,279
[I will.]

363
00:25:26,759 --> 00:25:27,680
[I remember once]

364
00:25:28,799 --> 00:25:31,200
[I said I was going to town]

365
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:33,640
[and shut down the salon
for a few days.]

366
00:25:36,119 --> 00:25:37,000
[Actually]

367
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:38,920
[I got a call from the police.]

368
00:25:40,039 --> 00:25:41,920
[They asked me to identify a body.]

369
00:25:57,359 --> 00:25:59,240
[Guodong owed a lot of money.]

370
00:26:03,519 --> 00:26:05,839
[To escape debt,]

371
00:26:06,759 --> 00:26:08,039
[he hid on a ship.]

372
00:26:09,359 --> 00:26:10,640
[He drank,]

373
00:26:11,279 --> 00:26:12,079
[got drunk,]

374
00:26:13,279 --> 00:26:15,319
[missed a step]

375
00:26:15,839 --> 00:26:17,039
[and fell into the sea.]

376
00:26:35,160 --> 00:26:37,759
I don't blame you for hiding it from me.

377
00:26:40,759 --> 00:26:42,519
Guodong

378
00:26:44,359 --> 00:26:47,400
caused us so much trouble.

379
00:26:50,160 --> 00:26:51,559
He made our lives

380
00:26:51,720 --> 00:26:54,119
a living hell.

381
00:26:59,720 --> 00:27:00,559
Lanfang,

382
00:27:02,240 --> 00:27:02,920
Wu.

383
00:27:06,599 --> 00:27:07,920
Thanks to you both,

384
00:27:09,119 --> 00:27:10,519
all these years,

385
00:27:11,680 --> 00:27:14,079
I've finally had a good life.

386
00:27:18,200 --> 00:27:19,640
I have no regrets.

387
00:27:21,720 --> 00:27:22,319
Wu.
Grandma.

388
00:27:25,599 --> 00:27:26,559
Wu,

389
00:27:30,160 --> 00:27:31,200
from now on,

390
00:27:32,359 --> 00:27:34,160
you've got to work hard.

391
00:27:35,519 --> 00:27:36,519
Got it?

392
00:27:37,920 --> 00:27:38,519
I will.

393
00:27:39,920 --> 00:27:40,559
I will for sure.

394
00:27:42,160 --> 00:27:42,799
Good.

395
00:27:58,119 --> 00:27:58,559
Wu.
Wu.

396
00:28:03,400 --> 00:28:04,319
Why are you here?

397
00:28:05,119 --> 00:28:06,279
I told you not to come,

398
00:28:06,279 --> 00:28:07,400
just stay home and study.

399
00:28:07,720 --> 00:28:08,319
You never listen.

400
00:28:09,079 --> 00:28:10,079
We came to see Grandma

401
00:28:10,279 --> 00:28:11,000
and you too.

402
00:28:13,240 --> 00:28:14,200
How is Grandma?

403
00:28:17,799 --> 00:28:19,119
She's not very clear-minded.

404
00:28:19,519 --> 00:28:20,640
Awake only sometimes.

405
00:28:21,279 --> 00:28:21,960
Even when she wakes up,
she may not recognize people.

406
00:28:28,519 --> 00:28:28,960
Oh right.

407
00:28:29,440 --> 00:28:30,519
The school issued exam passes.

408
00:28:30,920 --> 00:28:31,519
I brought yours.

409
00:28:32,759 --> 00:28:34,960
And the teachers
also gave prediction papers.

410
00:28:38,200 --> 00:28:39,400
Review them again

411
00:28:39,720 --> 00:28:40,519
before the exam.

412
00:28:48,759 --> 00:28:49,279
Thanks.

413
00:28:58,440 --> 00:28:59,000
Wu,

414
00:28:59,640 --> 00:29:00,279
should we

415
00:29:00,799 --> 00:29:01,839
tell Qing Ye about this?

416
00:29:02,519 --> 00:29:03,000
No.

417
00:29:04,440 --> 00:29:05,519
Don't tell her anything.

418
00:29:08,039 --> 00:29:08,599
Remember that.

419
00:29:10,200 --> 00:29:10,680
Alright.

420
00:30:18,720 --> 00:30:19,440
[Grandma!]

421
00:30:19,559 --> 00:30:21,079
[I found a big snail!]

422
00:30:27,519 --> 00:30:28,519
[So big!]

423
00:30:28,599 --> 00:30:30,599
[You're amazing!]

424
00:30:33,920 --> 00:30:35,319
[Let's look over there.]

425
00:30:35,400 --> 00:30:36,839
[There's some here too, yeah?]

426
00:30:53,440 --> 00:30:53,960
Grandma,

427
00:30:55,119 --> 00:30:56,559
Xuan Island's almost renovated.

428
00:30:58,079 --> 00:30:59,200
When you get better,

429
00:31:00,359 --> 00:31:01,759
we'll move into the new house.

430
00:31:03,680 --> 00:31:04,519
Didn't you say

431
00:31:05,319 --> 00:31:07,119
you wanted to thank Mazu
and the Dragon King?

432
00:31:08,359 --> 00:31:09,279
And the sunset.

433
00:31:10,200 --> 00:31:10,759
Look.

434
00:31:12,039 --> 00:31:12,640
The sunset.

435
00:31:14,079 --> 00:31:14,839
So beautiful.

436
00:31:17,359 --> 00:31:18,440
By then,

437
00:31:18,960 --> 00:31:20,720
we'll all live a happy life together.

438
00:31:23,559 --> 00:31:24,880
I've already lived

439
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:27,640
a blessed life.

440
00:31:30,599 --> 00:31:31,640
Even though

441
00:31:31,680 --> 00:31:33,599
we're not blood-related.

442
00:31:38,440 --> 00:31:40,599
Having a daughter

443
00:31:40,640 --> 00:31:42,000
and a grandson like you,

444
00:31:44,240 --> 00:31:45,799
I've got no regrets.

445
00:32:16,079 --> 00:32:16,680
Grandma.

446
00:32:21,200 --> 00:32:21,880
Grandma.

447
00:34:15,199 --> 00:34:15,800
Grandma,

448
00:34:18,320 --> 00:34:19,760
I brought you to see the sea.

449
00:34:28,119 --> 00:34:28,800
I know

450
00:34:31,360 --> 00:34:32,679
I'm not your biological grandson.

451
00:34:34,719 --> 00:34:35,679
To everyone else here,

452
00:34:36,719 --> 00:34:37,719
you're just an old lady

453
00:34:37,719 --> 00:34:39,039
who loves crafts.

454
00:34:40,760 --> 00:34:41,440
But I know,

455
00:34:42,039 --> 00:34:43,440
when you were young,

456
00:34:44,360 --> 00:34:45,239
you went to school.

457
00:34:46,960 --> 00:34:48,679
But you had a hard life.

458
00:34:49,800 --> 00:34:50,800
Your husband died early,

459
00:34:51,800 --> 00:34:52,880
you raised

460
00:34:53,400 --> 00:34:54,519
Xing Guodong alone.

461
00:34:55,239 --> 00:34:56,199
To survive,

462
00:34:56,719 --> 00:34:57,519
you farmed,

463
00:34:58,440 --> 00:34:59,320
worked as a fisherwoman,

464
00:35:00,159 --> 00:35:01,519
even as a sailor.

465
00:35:02,440 --> 00:35:03,719
You suffered so much.

466
00:35:05,519 --> 00:35:07,360
Even though we're not blood-related,

467
00:35:08,199 --> 00:35:09,000
and you knew

468
00:35:09,840 --> 00:35:11,199
I'm not your real grandson.

469
00:35:12,320 --> 00:35:13,239
But you've always treated me

470
00:35:13,880 --> 00:35:15,000
better than anyone else.

471
00:35:17,119 --> 00:35:18,440
Since the day I can remember,

472
00:35:20,039 --> 00:35:20,880
I've always considered you

473
00:35:20,880 --> 00:35:22,039
my real grandma,

474
00:35:23,320 --> 00:35:24,519
my closest, dearest grandma,

475
00:35:25,440 --> 00:35:26,519
and my benefactor.

476
00:35:31,159 --> 00:35:32,840
Every time I was at my lowest,

477
00:35:33,880 --> 00:35:35,679
you were always by my side,

478
00:35:37,880 --> 00:35:39,400
pulling me back from the edge

479
00:35:40,360 --> 00:35:41,159
of the cliff.

480
00:35:43,280 --> 00:35:44,800
I remember when I was little,

481
00:35:44,800 --> 00:35:45,719
once

482
00:35:46,360 --> 00:35:47,719
I secretly bought a piece of candy.

483
00:35:48,320 --> 00:35:49,840
Xing Guodong kicked me away.

484
00:35:51,559 --> 00:35:52,679
I just cried on the ground.

485
00:35:54,679 --> 00:35:57,519
You helped me up

486
00:35:58,719 --> 00:35:59,719
and comforted me:

487
00:36:00,440 --> 00:36:01,320
"Wu,

488
00:36:02,519 --> 00:36:03,000
be good.

489
00:36:04,000 --> 00:36:04,719
Don't cry.

490
00:36:06,840 --> 00:36:07,760
Have some candy

491
00:36:09,360 --> 00:36:10,280
and it won't feel bitter anymore."

492
00:36:12,199 --> 00:36:13,639
I also remember when I

493
00:36:15,360 --> 00:36:16,719
got seriously ill as a child.

494
00:36:18,320 --> 00:36:19,079
I had to go to the hospital

495
00:36:19,079 --> 00:36:20,639
for injections every day.

496
00:36:22,159 --> 00:36:23,440
Xing Guodong thought
I was a waste of money.

497
00:36:25,800 --> 00:36:26,519
Only you…

498
00:36:27,519 --> 00:36:29,079
But you couldn't bear to take a car.

499
00:36:33,159 --> 00:36:34,039
So you carried me.

500
00:36:35,119 --> 00:36:36,159
It was more than ten kilometers

501
00:36:36,159 --> 00:36:37,400
to the county town every day.

502
00:36:37,760 --> 00:36:39,400
And you carried me there again and again.

503
00:36:40,320 --> 00:36:41,320
But look at you,

504
00:36:42,519 --> 00:36:43,239
when you were sick,

505
00:36:44,320 --> 00:36:45,320
you didn't want treatment.

506
00:36:45,920 --> 00:36:46,559
When you broke your bone,

507
00:36:47,280 --> 00:36:48,639
you refused to get surgery.

508
00:36:49,840 --> 00:36:51,360
You were old, and your legs were weak,

509
00:36:51,960 --> 00:36:53,280
you still wouldn't buy a wheelchair.

510
00:36:54,400 --> 00:36:54,800
Fine,

511
00:36:55,360 --> 00:36:56,400
then I'll make one for you.

512
00:36:57,159 --> 00:36:58,719
I used a chair and wheels

513
00:36:58,719 --> 00:36:59,920
to build a wheelchair for you.

514
00:37:00,400 --> 00:37:01,119
But when you sat in it,

515
00:37:01,119 --> 00:37:02,159
didn't you notice?

516
00:37:03,079 --> 00:37:03,800
It's nowhere

517
00:37:04,400 --> 00:37:06,119
near as good as a real wheelchair.

518
00:37:07,840 --> 00:37:08,920
Last time I bought you

519
00:37:08,920 --> 00:37:09,960
a new electric wheelchair.

520
00:37:10,800 --> 00:37:11,719
You said it was

521
00:37:12,760 --> 00:37:13,519
I was being careless

522
00:37:14,079 --> 00:37:14,800
with money.

523
00:37:16,519 --> 00:37:17,519
But do you know how happy you were
sitting on it?

524
00:37:22,719 --> 00:37:23,320
At that time,

525
00:37:23,320 --> 00:37:24,639
I realized

526
00:37:25,239 --> 00:37:27,000
you always wanted
to go out and see the world.

527
00:37:30,920 --> 00:37:31,599
Grandma,

528
00:37:34,800 --> 00:37:35,760
you always said

529
00:37:38,679 --> 00:37:40,280
"Let's go gather shellfish."

530
00:37:42,119 --> 00:37:43,519
"Let's go see the sea."

531
00:37:44,440 --> 00:37:45,960
"Let's honor our promises."

532
00:37:47,440 --> 00:37:48,800
"Let's worship Mazu

533
00:37:49,159 --> 00:37:49,960
and the Dragon King."

534
00:37:50,280 --> 00:37:51,199
"Let's watch the sunset."

535
00:37:52,599 --> 00:37:53,559
After that,

536
00:37:59,039 --> 00:38:00,519
you never went out again.

537
00:38:09,159 --> 00:38:09,840
Grandma,

538
00:38:12,239 --> 00:38:13,159
in my next life,

539
00:38:16,000 --> 00:38:17,519
I still wanna be your grandson!

540
00:38:20,559 --> 00:38:21,320
In my next life,

541
00:38:23,800 --> 00:38:25,320
I'll still be your Wu!

542
00:38:29,679 --> 00:38:30,559
I promise

543
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:32,880
I won't let you

544
00:38:32,880 --> 00:38:34,199
suffer like this again!

545
00:39:06,719 --> 00:39:07,239
[Nice.]

546
00:39:07,760 --> 00:39:08,320
[Really nice.]

547
00:39:09,199 --> 00:39:10,719
[After all, I made it myself.]

548
00:39:20,079 --> 00:39:20,519
[Come.]

549
00:39:20,719 --> 00:39:22,199
[Take one each.]

550
00:39:22,599 --> 00:39:23,280
[Grandma,]

551
00:39:23,719 --> 00:39:25,519
[this flower steamed bun is so pretty!]

552
00:39:25,800 --> 00:39:27,239
[Your Auntie and I]

553
00:39:27,559 --> 00:39:29,079
[went to the Sea Goddess temple]

554
00:39:29,119 --> 00:39:29,880
[to pray for it.]

555
00:39:30,079 --> 00:39:31,159
[Eat it and you'll have sharp mind]

556
00:39:31,280 --> 00:39:32,519
[and clear eyes,]

557
00:39:32,599 --> 00:39:33,519
[and get good grades.]

558
00:39:33,679 --> 00:39:34,199
[Thank you, Grandma.]
[Thank you, Grandma.]

559
00:40:27,360 --> 00:40:29,360
Kids, do your best on the exam!

560
00:40:29,400 --> 00:40:30,880
Try to get a good score in the exams

561
00:40:30,920 --> 00:40:32,639
and bring honor to our Zhazhating!

562
00:40:32,880 --> 00:40:33,639
- Sure!
- Bring honor!
Thanks, Dad.

563
00:40:34,079 --> 00:40:35,039
Don't be nervous.

564
00:40:35,159 --> 00:40:36,440
Stay calm.

565
00:40:36,519 --> 00:40:37,599
Don't stress.

566
00:40:37,719 --> 00:40:38,800
Show your real ability.

567
00:40:38,800 --> 00:40:39,239
Exactly!

568
00:40:39,519 --> 00:40:40,440
Believe in yourselves!

569
00:40:40,639 --> 00:40:41,400
What does this mean?

570
00:40:41,440 --> 00:40:43,199
Mom, what's this for?

571
00:40:43,440 --> 00:40:45,079
"Go for gold" charm!

572
00:40:46,199 --> 00:40:46,800
Right!

573
00:40:46,960 --> 00:40:48,519
Life should have a little ritual.

574
00:40:48,679 --> 00:40:50,679
We even wore cheongsams today.

575
00:40:50,880 --> 00:40:54,000
- Cheongsam's on, luck is on!
- Cheongsam's on, luck is on!

576
00:40:54,639 --> 00:40:55,840
It's the kids' exam day.

577
00:40:55,840 --> 00:40:57,280
Why are you so excited?

578
00:40:57,280 --> 00:40:58,199
I'm nervous!
Can't you tell?

579
00:40:59,239 --> 00:40:59,920
Nervous?
Don't be!

580
00:41:00,920 --> 00:41:01,400
Son,

581
00:41:01,920 --> 00:41:02,679
listen up.

582
00:41:02,960 --> 00:41:03,920
Just take the exam casually.

583
00:41:04,119 --> 00:41:05,119
We don't expect

584
00:41:05,159 --> 00:41:05,960
that much from you.

585
00:41:06,840 --> 00:41:08,639
Maybe I'll be the dark horse!

586
00:41:09,360 --> 00:41:10,400
I'll give it my all.

587
00:41:10,440 --> 00:41:11,000
Listen,
just do your best.

588
00:41:13,039 --> 00:41:13,639
The bus is here.

589
00:41:14,119 --> 00:41:14,719
Come!

590
00:41:14,800 --> 00:41:16,280
Come!

591
